-- Erste Group swings to H1 loss of 929.7 mln euros
-- By Michael Shields
-- Thu Jul 31, 2014 01:47AM EDT
-- None



VIENNA, July 31 (Reuters) - Austria's Erste Group Bank <ERST.VI> swung to a first-half loss of 929.7 million euros ($1.25 billion) as it booked impairment charges and set aside 130 million euros for a Hungarian law forcing banks to compensate customers for mispriced loans.

